  "texts": [
    "From [x] ≃ R ≃ i [y] ≃, we have ∃x ′ ∈ [x] ≃ ∃y ′ ∈ [y] ≃: x ′ R i y ′.From [y] ≃ ̸ ∈ X ≃, we have y ̸ ∈ X.",
    "Since X ∈ RO(F), together y ̸ ∈ X and y ≃ s y ′ imply y ′ ̸ ∈ X by Fact 4.2, which with x ′ R i y ′ implies x ′ ̸ ∈ ■ i X.",
    "Then since ■ i X ∈ RO(F), together x ′ ̸ ∈ ■ i X and x ≃ s x ′ imply x ̸ ∈ ■ i X by Fact 4.2, so [x] ≃ ̸ ∈ (■ i X) ≃.Since F is a partial-state frame, P is closed under ∩, ⊃, and ■ i.",
    "It follows from (i)-(iii) and the definition of P ≃ that P ≃ is also closed under ∩, ⊃ ≃, and ■ ≃ i, so F ≃ is a partial-state frame.",
    "Since we also showed above that P ≃ ⊆ RO(F ≃), we conclude that F ≃ is a possibility frame."
